Paper: hep-th/0204149

Date: 2002-04-18

Title: Non-commutative Oscillators and the commutative limit

Authors: B.Muthukumar and P.Mitra

Comments: Latex, 6 pages, Minor changes and references added

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D66 (2002) 027701

It is shown in first order perturbation theory that anharmonic oscillators innon-commutative space behave smoothly in the commutative limit just as harmonicoscillators do. The non-commutativity provides a method for converting aproblem in degenerate perturbation theory to a non-degenerate problem.